# Deploy and PPT sync on every update

Whenever the user asks for product/feature/UI/backend changes (or says “update”), finish the implementation by **always** updating all four channels before ending the turn:

1. **GitHub** — commit relevant files (never commit secrets or `~$*.pptx` lock files) and `git push` to `origin` (usually `main`).
2. **Vercel** — from `Frontend/`, run `vercel --prod --yes` so https://ushirika-sme-portal.vercel.app picks up the UI.
3. **Render** — ensure the API on https://ushirika-api.onrender.com reflects the push (auto-deploy from GitHub). If `/api/health` still shows an old `version`, trigger a redeploy (empty commit or dashboard) and re-check until `version` matches `Backend/app/__init__.py`.
4. **PPT** — update `Presentation/build_defence_pptx.py` for any user-visible or methodological change, then run it to regenerate:
   - `Presentation/Ushirika_Group15_Defence_Presentation.pptx`
   - (or `Ushirika_Group15_Defence_v13.pptx` if the main file is locked open)
   Include the rebuilt `.pptx` in the same GitHub commit/push when possible.

## Checklist before saying “done”

- [ ] Code committed and pushed
- [ ] Vercel production deploy succeeded
- [ ] Render `/api/health` version matches the release bump
- [ ] Defence PPT rebuilt and pushed (or saved to alt path if locked)

## Notes

- Bump `Backend/app/__init__.__version__` on meaningful backend releases so Render health proves the new build.
- Keep the defence deck ≤ 12 slides; prefer editing the builder script over hand-editing the `.pptx`.
- Do not skip these steps unless the user explicitly says not to deploy or not to touch the PPT.
